title: 460 Dead 243,612 Reported Injuries from COVID19 Vaccines Reported in the U.K.
cleaned_text:
The UK Government’s reporting system for COVID jjab adverse reactions from the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency released their latest report today, March 4, 2021.

The report covers data collected from December 9, 2020, through February 21, 2021, for the two experimental COVID jjabs currently in use in the U.K. from Pfizer and AstraZeneca.

They report a total of 460 deaths and 243,612 injuries.

For the COVID-19 mRNA Pfizer- BioNTech jjab analysis they report:

Total reactions for the COVID-19 mRNA Pfizer- BioNTech jjab: 212 deaths and 85,179 injuries

For the COVID-19 jjab Oxford University/AstraZeneca analysis they report:

Total reactions for the COVID-19 jjab Oxford University/AstraZenec jjab: 244 deaths and 157,637 injuries

For the COVID-19 jjab brand unspecified analysis they report:

Total reactions for the COVID-19 jjab brand unspecified jjabs: 4 deaths and 796 injuries

The overall safety experience with both jjabs is so far as expected from the clinical trials.

Based on current experience, the expected benefits of both COVID-19 jjabs in preventing COVID-19 and its serious complications far outweigh any known side effects.
